The article discusses the need to address the border crisis and proposes a bipartisan bill as a solution. The bill aims to enact the toughest and fairest reforms to secure the border, granting the President emergency authority to shut down the border when overwhelmed. The article also emphasizes the need for Congress to provide funding to secure the border, including additional border patrol agents, immigration judges, asylum officers, and inspection machines. The author argues that passing a bipartisan bill is the way to effectively address the border crisis.